  <title translate="true">Update Readme.txt</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Update Readme.txt</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Update Readme.txt</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This command copies the readme.txt file specified on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Readme.txt_File" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Readme.txt File</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane to the directory specified on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Create_Archive" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Create Archive</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane and then appends descriptions of the files and folders from the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Archive_Structure" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Archive Structure</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane to the end of the file. This command is useful when either the file descriptions on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Create_Archive" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Create Archive</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane or the content of the readme.txt file specified on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Readme.txt_File" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Readme.txt File</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane have changed after the archive has been created.</text></para>
  </body>
